WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.000
I'm sorry, Robbie.

00:07.000 --> 00:14.000
Sorry to be late this morning, but, uh, well, we've still got some time for a cup of coffee.

00:14.000 --> 00:19.000
I can't wait to see my old pal Charlie Rayford. Neither can I.

00:30.500 --> 00:32.000
So you thought about it, huh?

00:32.000 --> 00:34.000
Yes, I have, Dad.

00:34.000 --> 00:39.000
Well, I'm glad. I knew you'd realize that this interview could be an important experience for you.

00:39.000 --> 00:41.000
I came to that conclusion.

00:41.000 --> 00:44.000
That's very wise, Robbie.

00:44.000 --> 00:46.000
Very wise.

00:46.000 --> 00:50.000
Now let's, uh, let's head off to the City of University Club.

00:50.000 --> 00:53.000
Thanks, Dad. Thanks.

00:53.000 --> 00:54.000
For what?

00:54.000 --> 00:56.000
Thanks for hearing me out.

00:56.000 --> 00:57.000
And...

00:57.000 --> 00:58.000
And...

00:58.000 --> 01:01.000
And thanks for being such an understanding, Father.

01:01.000 --> 01:04.000
Well, thank you, Robbie.

01:04.000 --> 01:06.000
Thank you.

01:18.000 --> 01:20.000
Hello, Stuart.

01:20.000 --> 01:21.000
It's great to see you.

01:21.000 --> 01:23.000
Charlie Rayford?

01:23.000 --> 01:25.000
You look as young as ever.

01:27.000 --> 01:30.000
You must be Robbie.

01:30.000 --> 01:31.000
All right.

01:31.000 --> 01:34.000
Yes, this is my younger son, Robbie.

01:34.000 --> 01:39.000
Robbie, I want you to meet one of the best tennis players on the Michigan team.

01:39.000 --> 01:42.000
Charlie Rayford. Nice to meet you, Dean Rayford.

01:42.000 --> 01:45.000
Well, he was good at tennis players, your dad.

01:45.000 --> 01:48.000
Now, I'm not very good at it.

01:48.000 --> 01:50.000
Frankly, neither was I.

01:50.000 --> 01:52.000
Charlie was a story of the team.

01:52.000 --> 01:54.000
Thanks.

01:54.000 --> 01:56.000
Well, have you been, Philip?

01:56.000 --> 01:59.000
Oh, working too hard.

01:59.000 --> 02:00.000
Doesn't show?

02:00.000 --> 02:01.000
How's Ellen?

02:01.000 --> 02:03.000
Fine, thank you.

02:03.000 --> 02:05.000
And how's March?

02:05.000 --> 02:09.000
She's still giving the toughest English history exams in the school.

02:09.000 --> 02:12.000
And loving every minute of it.

02:12.000 --> 02:18.000
And speaking of minutes, I have interviews until noon, so why don't we get right to work?

02:18.000 --> 02:21.000
Can you, uh, can you have lunch with this later?

02:21.000 --> 02:23.000
I'd love to have felt but I'm afraid I can't.

02:23.000 --> 02:27.000
I'm only here two days and I have interviews with 26 applicants.

02:27.000 --> 02:28.000
I understand.

02:28.000 --> 02:29.000
Well, thanks.

02:29.000 --> 02:32.000
I'll, uh, I'll wait outside.

02:32.000 --> 02:34.000
Good luck, son.

02:34.000 --> 02:36.000
Did you bring your transcript from high school?

02:36.000 --> 02:37.000
Yes, sir.

02:37.000 --> 02:38.000
Right here.

02:38.000 --> 02:40.000
Thank you.

02:40.000 --> 02:42.000
Please sit down.

02:46.000 --> 02:49.000
I see under activities that you've been writing for the school paper.

02:49.000 --> 02:51.000
Yes, sir.

02:51.000 --> 02:54.000
What kind of articles have you written?

02:54.000 --> 02:55.000
All kinds.

02:55.000 --> 02:58.000
Sports, um, editorials, theater reviews.

02:58.000 --> 02:59.000
You name it.

02:59.000 --> 03:00.000
I've written it.

03:00.000 --> 03:01.000
Hmm.

03:01.000 --> 03:04.000
Well, have you ever thought of becoming a journalist?

03:04.000 --> 03:06.000
Professional writer?

03:06.000 --> 03:08.000
Not until recently.

03:08.000 --> 03:11.000
Michigan is a fine school of journalism.

03:11.000 --> 03:14.000
Yes, I know that.

03:14.000 --> 03:17.000
You seem to have some reservations.

03:17.000 --> 03:19.000
I'm a little uncertain.

03:19.000 --> 03:23.000
And it's been very nice talking to you.

03:23.000 --> 03:25.000
Nice talking to you, sir.

03:25.000 --> 03:28.000
One piece of advice.

03:28.000 --> 03:33.000
The most important thing is for you to decide your own future.

03:33.000 --> 03:34.000
Yes, sir.

03:34.000 --> 03:36.000
Goodbye, Dean Raffer.

03:36.000 --> 03:37.000
Goodbye, Robbie.

03:37.000 --> 03:39.000
Good luck.

